clue: In song, it was used to describe an arachnid making its way up a drainage pipe

response: itsy-bitsy

clue: It's a planned function where someone famous is introduced to & socializes with audience members

response: meet & greet

clue: Definitions of this include a country at war, a new night club, a good place for Wi-Fi

response: a hot spot

clue: This bit of advice could be translated as "pretend to be successful until you become so"

response: fake it till you make it

clue: A police helicopter providing surveillance is idiomatically one of these & doesn't need to blink either

response: an eye in the sky

